experience: Some previous work-related skill, knowledge, or experience is usually needed. For example, a teller would benefit from experience working directly with the public.
education: These occupations usually require a high school diploma.
job_training: Employees in these occupations need anywhere from a few months to one year of working with experienced employees. A recognized apprenticeship program may be associated with these occupations.
example: These occupations often involve using your knowledge and skills to help others. Examples include orderlies, counter and rental clerks, customer service representatives, security guards, upholsterers, tellers, and dental laboratory technicians.
svp_desc: Individuals workers typically need anywhere from minimum of 3 and 6 months- up to 2 years- to learn the techniques, acquire the information, and develop the facility needed for average performance in specific situations.

work_tasks.title: Woodworking Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Except Sawing
work_tasks.task: Start machines, adjust controls, and make trial cuts to ensure that machinery is operating properly.
work_tasks.descr: Start machines, adjust controls, and make trial cuts to ensure that machinery is operating properly.

work_tasks.title: Woodworking Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Except Sawing
work_tasks.task: Determine product specifications and materials, work methods, and machine setup requirements, according to blueprints, oral or written instructions, drawings, or work orders.
work_tasks.descr: Determine product specifications and materials, work methods, and machine setup requirements, according to blueprints, oral or written instructions, drawings, or work orders.

work_tasks.title: Woodworking Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Except Sawing
work_tasks.task: Feed stock through feed mechanisms or conveyors into planing, shaping, boring, mortising, or sanding machines to produce desired components.
work_tasks.descr: Feed stock through feed mechanisms or conveyors into planing, shaping, boring, mortising, or sanding machines to produce desired components.

work_tasks.title: Woodworking Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Except Sawing
work_tasks.task: Adjust machine tables or cutting devices and set controls on machines to produce specified cuts or operations.
work_tasks.descr: Adjust machine tables or cutting devices and set controls on machines to produce specified cuts or operations.

work_tasks.title: Woodworking Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Except Sawing
work_tasks.task: Monitor operation of machines and make adjustments to correct problems and ensure conformance to specifications.
work_tasks.descr: Monitor operation of machines and make adjustments to correct problems and ensure conformance to specifications.

work_tasks.title: Woodworking Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Except Sawing
work_tasks.task: Set up, program, operate, or tend computerized or manual woodworking machines, such as drill presses, lathes, shapers, routers, sanders, planers, or wood-nailing machines.

work_tasks.descr: Examine finished workpieces for smoothness, shape, angle, depth-of-cut, or conformity to specifications and verify dimensions, visually and using hands, rules, calipers, templates, or gauges.
